   188	6. **Embedder unchanged.** The `EmbedderIdentity` contract,
   189	   `VaryingEmbedder`, and the profile-pinning logic at
   190	   `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3248-3260` are
   191	   not touched. HITL Q2 in
   192	   `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § HITL responses
   193	   locked: KEEP existing embedder. Tier-1 #3 (smaller
   194	   embeddings) and Tier-1 #5 (matryoshka) are out of scope
   195	   for 0.7.0.
   196	
   197	7. **Single-writer + projection-cursor contracts preserved.**
   198	   Both column inserts commit in the same writer transaction at
   199	   the `_fathomdb_vector_rows` insert site near
   200	   `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2846`. The
   201	   writer-loop pins at `:2174` and `:2242` are not touched.
   202	   AC-017 / AC-018 / AC-020 behavior is preserved.
   203	
   204	## 3. Alternatives considered (and rejected)
   205	
   206	Each alternative below was considered against the AC-013 gap; the
   207	research doc carries the long-form analysis.
   208	
   209	- **Vectorlite (HNSW SQLite extension).** Mechanism: load a
   210	  separate `USING vectorlite(...)` virtual table backed by an
   211	  HNSW graph stored in shadow tables. Rejected because the
   212	  upstream has had no release since 2024-08-19, has no
   213	  published 1 M × 768 benchmark, and counts as a structural
   214	  architectural lever stacked on top of PCACHE2 — violates the
   215	  one-architectural-lever-per-release rule. Cited:
   216	  `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § Tier 2.
   217	
   218	- **sqlite-vec ANN alpha (v0.1.10-alpha.1).** Mechanism: use
   219	  the upstream-experimental ANN indices (`rescore`, `ivf`,
   220	  `DiskANN`). Rejected because the release is alpha-tagged and
   221	  upstream classifies it as not production-ready. Cited:
   222	  `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § Tier 3,
   223	  sqlite-vec releases.
   224	
   225	- **Rust-side `usearch` / `instant-distance`.** Mechanism:
   226	  pull KNN out of SQLite into a Rust-side ANN library and
   227	  rebuild the search verb around it. Rejected because the
   228	  blast radius (leaving SQLite for the KNN step, snapshot /
   229	  freshness handshake redesign, AC-017 cursor-freshness
   230	  re-derivation) is far larger than two packs of in-place
   231	  schema + query work, and the data-encoding lever closes the
   232	  gap without it. Cited:
   233	  `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § Tier 3 (integration
   234	  shape C).
   235	
   236	- **Embedder swap (dim reduction 768 → 384 or 256).**
   237	  Mechanism: replace `VaryingEmbedder` with a smaller embedder
   238	  to shrink bytes-per-row. Rejected by HITL Q2 lock 2026-05-27:
   239	  keep existing embedder. Rationale: switching embedders
   240	  requires a profile rotation through
   241	  `_fathomdb_embedder_profiles` and a corpus rebuild
   242	  (writer-cooperation cost), and even at dim 128 the
   243	  arithmetic-only saving is ~6× — well short of the ~25–40×
   244	  gap. Cited:
   245	  `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § Tier 1 #3,
   246	  § HITL responses.
   247	
   248	- **Partitioning alone (metadata prefilter / partition_key
   249	  without quantization).** Mechanism: keep the f32 column,
   250	  add `source_type` partition_key + metadata columns, push
   251	  filters into the WHERE clause. Rejected as load-bearing:
   252	  the AC-013 fixture is single-kind, so partitioning yields
   253	  zero benefit at the gate. Partitioning is **kept** as a
   254	  bundled deliverable in Pack 1 because it is the correct
   255	  shape for real workloads and avoids a second migration in
   256	  0.7.1 — but it does not close the gate on its own. Cited:
   257	  `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § Tier 1 #1, #2.
   258	
   259	## 4. Consequences
   260	
   261	- **Schema change (Pack 1).** `vector_default` gains the
   262	  `embedding_bin bit[768]` column, the `source_type` vec0
   263	  partition_key, and additional metadata columns (within the
   264	  vec0 16-column budget). Migration is a one-pass
   265	  `INSERT … SELECT vec_quantize_binary(embedding) FROM
   266	  vector_default` populating the bit column for the existing
   267	  corpus. Migration cost: ~3 GB read + ~96 MB write on the
   268	  1 M-row test corpus; ~64 s on the dev box per the handoff
   269	  estimate, well under the workflow timeout.
   270	
   271	- **Ingest cost (Pack 1).** The writer at the
   272	  `_fathomdb_vector_rows` insert site near
   273	  `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2846` performs
   274	  a single additional `vec_quantize_binary()` and one extra
   275	  column write per row inside the same writer transaction.
   276	  No new commit; no new lock; no new SQLite handle. The
   277	  single-writer + projection-cursor freshness contract is
   278	  preserved bit-for-bit. Storage grows by ~3 % (96 B per row
   279	  on top of the 3072 B f32 footprint).
   280	
   281	- **Query-path rewrite (Pack 2).** Replace
   282	  `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2317-2323` with
   283	  the two-phase shape outlined in
   284	  `dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PERF-VECTOR-QUANT-HANDOFF.md` § 2.2.
   285	  No change to the writer side, no change to the projection-
   286	  cursor handshake, no change to `register_sqlite_vec_extension`
   287	  at `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3107`. K = 64
   288	  is named as a constant for future tuning.
   289	
   290	- **Recall floor enforced as a RED test.** A new perf-gates
   291	  test (e.g. `ac_NNN_recall_at_10`) computes brute-force f32
   292	  ground truth at test-setup against the retained f32 column,
   293	  runs the production search path, and asserts
   294	  `recall@10 ≥ 0.90` on the AC-013 fixture. Lands RED in
   295	  Pack 2.1 alongside the latency budget re-pin
   296	  (`tests/perf_gates.rs:149-150` → 80 / 300 ms) and must
   297	  remain RED at canonical-CI N = 1 M scale until Pack 2.2's
   298	  query rewrite lands. Both gates GREEN at canonical-CI is
   299	  the Pack 2 close criterion. (0.7.2: the 0.90 floor is kept and
   300	  now VALIDATED against the real embedder — corrected ANN-fidelity
   301	  recall@10 = 0.937, full CI above 0.90; see § 2 point 4. A fast
   302	  sentinel `ac_013b_floor_matches_adr` pins the constant to this
   303	  ADR.)
   304	
   305	- **AC-019 carry.** The existing 10× bound on AC-019 stays
   306	  unchanged; the same two-phase query shape benefits AC-019
   307	  proportionally. AC-019 is expected to improve substantially
   308	  but no new bound is pinned here.
   309	
   310	- **AC-012 / AC-017 / AC-018 / AC-020 unchanged.** The
   311	  writer-loop pins (`:2174`, `:2242`), the embedder profile
   312	  table, and the reader-pool concurrency surface are all
   313	  untouched. Pack 1 changes schema but not query semantics, so
   314	  these tests stay GREEN through both packs.
   315	
   316	- **Post-0.7.0 follow-ups.** Graph-index ANN (vectorlite,
   317	  sqlite-vec ANN alpha, Rust-side `usearch`) and
   318	  matryoshka / smaller-embedder work are tracked in
   319	  `dev/notes/pcache2-followups.md` for 0.7.1+ if real-workload
   320	  telemetry shows the binary-quant scan is insufficient.
   321	
   322	## 5. Architectural-lever accounting
   323	
   324	The 0.7.0 architectural lever is **`SQLITE_CONFIG_PCACHE2`**, locked
   325	by `dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-ac020-architectural-lever.md`. The decision
   326	in § 2 of this ADR is a **data-encoding change** (schema +
   327	quantization function + two-phase SQL), not a second architectural
   328	lever:
   329	
   330	- It does not change the SQLite build, the SQLite vendor, the WAL
   331	  format, or the page-cache allocator.
   332	- It does not change the reader-pool topology, the writer-lock
   333	  shape, the projection-cursor contract, or the snapshot-freshness
   334	  contract.
   335	- It does not change the embedder identity or the profile-pinning
   336	  protocol.
   337	- It changes only the bytes stored per row in the vec0 table and
   338	  the SQL the reader emits against it.
   339	
   340	This disposition is reaffirmed verbatim from
   341	`dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § "Architectural-lever
   342	accounting". The HITL doc records the same call.
   343	
   344	**Fallback.** If a future reviewer (codex or HITL) counts
   345	binary-quant + rerank as a second architectural lever stacked on
   346	PCACHE2, the agreed fallback per the handoff and the research doc
   347	is to ship **Pack 1 only in 0.7.0** (schema migration + ingest
   348	double-write; no reader behavior change; AC-013 stays at
   349	2048 / 2327 ms) and slip **Pack 2 to 0.7.1** (query rewrite + RED
   350	tests + lock-flip). The Pack 1-only shape preserves the on-disk
   351	shape for the future Pack 2 cutover and avoids a second migration.
   352	Escalation trigger is called out in
   353	`dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PERF-VECTOR-QUANT-HANDOFF.md` § "Open
   354	items the implementing agent should escalate to HITL".
   355	
