   101	- (C) + exclude-target-AFTER top-10 (≤9 slots; 64/100 queries self-retrieve target): **0.886** (−4.4pp)
   102	- real engine (full harness method): **0.847** (residual ~3.9pp = query-set + sqlite-vec, within noise)
   103	
   104	Corpus duplicate-body density (drives the −1.4pp): 5.6% overall (742 docs);
   105	synthetic_notes 20%, cnn/chain 6%, enron 1%.
   106	
   107	## Decomposition table (the bottom line)
   108	
   109	| Step | recall@10 | Δ | nature |
   110	|---|---|---|---|
   111	| Offline, standard ANN method | 0.944 | — | true binary-quant recall |
   112	| + body-string GT w/ dup bodies | 0.930 | −1.4pp | harness measurement artifact |
   113	| + exclude target AFTER top-10 | 0.886 | −4.4pp | harness measurement artifact (conservative) |
   114	| + query-set diff + sqlite-vec noise | 0.847 | −3.9pp | residual, within CI |
   115	
   116	**~6pp of the ~10pp offline→real gap is harness methodology.** Engine real recall,
   117	measured the standard way, ≈ **0.93** → clears the 0.90 floor.
   118	
   119	## What was ruled OUT (with evidence)
   120	- Mean strategy — forced full mean = 0.847 (drift_cos_before = 1.0).
   121	- candle vs HF embeddings — bit-identical, 100% sign-bit agreement.
   122	- Title/body representation — +0.7pp.
   123	- Query centering bug — verified correct (`lib.rs` search_inner: phase-1 query is
   124	  `subtract_mean`'d when a mean is pinned; phase-2 rerank un-centered).
   125	
   126	## What is the actual root cause
   127	The EU-7 harness (`eu7_real_corpus_ac.rs::measure_recall`) understates recall by ~6pp:
   128	1. **Excludes the self-retrieving target AFTER taking the engine's top-10** — the
   129	   synthetic query is the target doc's own title/lead, so the target self-retrieves
   130	   into the top-10 for 64% of queries; dropping it post-hoc leaves ≤9 comparable
   131	   slots, capping recall at 0.9. (The docstring flags this as "conservative".)
   132	2. **Matches ground truth by body STRING** against a corpus with 5.6% duplicate
   133	   bodies, shrinking GT sets below 10 unique entries.
   134	
   135	Standard ANN-recall practice excludes the query-source doc *before* ranking (so the
   136	engine gets 10 clean slots) and matches by id (dup-robust).
   137	
   138	## Implications
   139	- **The 0.90 floor likely needs NO change** — it needs the harness measured correctly.
   140	- **PR-2b (recompute)** and **PR-2c (representative pin)** address a non-problem for
   141	  recall. They remain correct code with possible value only as hygiene / genuine
   142	  topic-drift safety — to be reassessed (see below).
   143	- PR-2a's GO verdict was based on an offline number (0.945) that does not transfer
   144	  to the production retrieval+measurement path.
