   147	1. **(this doc)** capture findings. ✅
   148	2. **Fix the harness + re-measure** (gold-standard confirmation): patch
   149	   `eu7_real_corpus_ac.rs` to exclude the query-source doc *before* the top-10
   150	   (retrieve top-(10+1), drop target, take 10) and match GT by id/dedup, then
   151	   re-run release. Expect ~0.90–0.93.
   152	3. **Reassess PR-2b/PR-2c** — measure whether each makes a positive / negative /
   153	   neutral difference to (correctly-measured) recall, and decide ship vs shelve.
   154	
   155	## Residual risks / caveats
   156	- The ~3.9pp residual (offline harness-method 0.886 vs real 0.847) is not fully
   157	  isolated; attributed to query-set RNG difference + minor sqlite-vec vec0 bit-KNN
   158	  candidate suboptimality. The fixed-harness re-measure will tighten this.
   159	- All real-engine numbers are dev-box scouting (N=7667, 100 synthetic queries);
   160	  canonical N=1M with relevance-judged queries remains PR-3.
   161	
   162	## Follow-up TODO: log the silent ground-truth-embed phase in the EU-7 harness
   163	
   164	**Symptom:** during a full run, `eu7_real_corpus_ac.rs` goes silent for ~25-45 min
   165	*after* the last `EU7_SEED_PROGRESS` line and *before* `seed_done`. Twice this
   166	looked like a hang and once prompted a premature kill. It is NOT a hang: the
   167	harness re-embeds the entire corpus single-threaded to build the in-Rust f32
   168	ground truth (`for body in &bodies[seeded..actual_n] { doc_vecs.push(embedder.embed(body)) }`),
   169	which emits no output. At ~0.3-0.4 s/doc single-threaded that is ~45 min for 7667
   170	docs, with zero log lines.
   171	
   172	**Fix (minimal but useful):** a single line literally *between* the loop and the
   173	`seed_done` print only fires once (an end-marker) and does NOT break the silence
   174	*during* the loop -- so "between" alone is not the useful placement. Add instead:
   175	1. a `GT_EMBED_START n=<n>` line before the loop, and
   176	2. a **periodic progress line inside the loop**, mirroring `EU7_SEED_PROGRESS`
   177	   (every ~30 s or every K docs: `EU7_GT_EMBED_PROGRESS embedded=i/n rate_docs_per_s=...`).
   178	   A throttled `Instant`-based report like the seed loop already uses is enough.
   179	This makes the longest unlogged stretch observable and stops it reading as a wedge.
   180	Cheap, test-only, no behavior change. (The single end-marker between the loop and
   181	`seed_done` is a fine additional cheap minimum, but the in-loop periodic line is
   182	the one that matters.)

