## Verdict: PASS

### 1. [info] No findings in requested scope
Refs: [perf_gates.rs:156](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S3-20260531T131418Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:156), [perf_gates.rs:572](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S3-20260531T131418Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:572), [perf_gates.rs:662](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S3-20260531T131418Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:662), [ADR §2 pt 4](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S3-20260531T131418Z/dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-vector-binary-quant.md:124), [ADR §4](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S3-20260531T131418Z/dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-vector-binary-quant.md:290), [ADR §6-§7](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S3-20260531T131418Z/dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-vector-binary-quant.md:356)
`AC013B_RECALL_FLOOR` remains `0.90` and was not raised. The new sentinel is genuinely fast and non-gated: it does not seed data, does not branch on `long_run_enabled()`, and asserts the constant stays `0.90` as documented in the ADR.

The ADR amendment is honest and explicit. It anchors validation on corrected ANN-fidelity `0.937 (CI 0.913-0.957)` against exact f32 top-10 over the same model, cites the harness-methodology correction to the root-cause doc, and separately frames EU-8 IR `0.571` as an embedder/task ceiling, not a gate or an ANN-quality claim.

I found no inconsistency in §6 or §7 with keeping the floor at `0.90`. The lock-flip language still requires the recall-floor test to be green at `>= 0.90`, and the §6 K-selection note now argues against further K-tuning on the basis of ANN-fidelity already exceeding the IR ceiling.

**What passed on inspection**
- The slice matches the ratified reframe in [decision memo §4](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S3-20260531T131418Z/dev/plans/runs/0.7.2-PR-2bc-decision.md:178) and the S3 spec in [floor-reframe prompt](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S3-20260531T131418Z/dev/plans/prompts/0.7.2-PR-2bc-S3-floor-reframe.md:28).
- The ANN-vs-IR distinction is consistent with the evidence docs: [root-cause “measure under discussion”](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S3-20260531T131418Z/dev/plans/runs/0.7.2-PR-2c-recall-rootcause.md:49) and [EU-8 synthesis](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S3-20260531T131418Z/dev/plans/runs/0.7.2-EU-8-ir-recall-results.md:42).
- The `+7.8pp` methodology explanation is carried into the ADR in the requested form, tied back to exclude-before plus dedup-GT versus exclude-after plus body-string GT.
- The two commits in scope are cleanly separated: `a154037` for test/comment work, then `78164b9` for ADR/output-artifact docs.

**Reviewer process notes**
- `MEMORY.md` was not present in this worktree, so I reviewed from the provided `AGENTS.md` instructions plus the required slice documents.
- I did not rerun `cargo build` or tests in this read-only review; the PASS is based on source inspection of the landed changes and the cited artifacts.
